CONTRIBUTING.md

# Contributing to KeralaGovLinks

We’re building a **safe, citizen-first gateway** to Kerala Government services—and we’d love your help!

## Ways to Contribute

### 1. Suggest Verified Links
- Go to `src/data/verifiedLinks.json`
- Add your entry following this format:
```json
{
  "title": "eDistrict Portal",
  "url": "https://edistrict.kerala.gov.in",
  "category": "Citizen Services",
  "source": "Govt of Kerala",
  "language": "English",
  "lastVerified": "2025-05-10"
}

Submit a pull request OR raise an issue with your link suggestion.


2. Improve UI/UX

Open src/components/ and submit improvements to layout, icons, or responsiveness.

We use Tailwind CSS (or insert actual styling tech here).


3. Translate to Malayalam

Add ml.json under src/i18n/ (or relevant localization folder)

Translate UI strings or guides


4. Fix Bugs or Add Features

Check open Issues

Create a feature branch and submit a Pull Request (PR)


5. Spread Awareness

Share the idea on social media

Help elderly or rural folks use the platform

Suggest this to Akshaya Centers or community leaders


Development Setup

1. Clone the repo:



git clone https://github.com/yourname/keralagovlinks.git

2. Install dependencies:



npm install

3. Start dev server:



npm run dev

Code Style

Follow ESLint + Prettier rules (configured in project)

Use clean, readable commit messages

Write small, focused pull requests


License

This project is MIT licensed. That means anyone can use, remix, or contribute—just be respectful.


---

Thank you for contributing to a safer digital Kerala!

